location.name: Carriage road at Jordon Pond, Mount Desert US-ME 44.32362, -68.25595

mediaNotes:
Adult male Swainson’s Thrush that was foraging on the ground that then flew up to a dead branch near the base of a spruce and began counter singing with a nearby conspecific. He just sat there singing and moving his head as if looking around. At the break, he dropped to the forest floor for a minute and then hopped back up to another perch close to where he had been sitting. It was fascinating to be able to watch him sing at such close range.
Any amplitude changes in his songs were the result of him modulating his efforts. I was focused directly on him during the entire cut.
Recorder HPF on at 80Hz, -12dB/octave.
